          <p>Raw counts are normalized to <strong>complaints per 100,000 residents</strong> using 2025 U.S. Census Bureau population estimates, so boroughs of different sizes can be compared fairly. The loudest borough is the one with the highest per-capita rate.</p>
          <p>Population figures are from the <a href="https://s-media.nyc.gov/agencies/dcp/assets/files/pdf/data-tools/population/population-estimates/new-york-city-population-estimates-and-trends-march-2026.pdf" target="_blank">U.S. Census Bureau Population Estimates Program, Vintage 2025</a> (July 1, 2025 estimates), via NYC Department of City Planning: Bronx 1,406,332 &middot; Brooklyn 2,653,963 &middot; Manhattan 1,664,862 &middot; Queens 2,358,182 &middot; Staten Island 501,290.</p>
